statement:
Let

\begin{align*}A = \begin{bmatrix}
1 & 3 \\ 3 & 8
\end{bmatrix}
\qquad 
B = \begin{bmatrix}
1 & 0 & -1 \\ -3 & 1 & 0
\end{bmatrix}\end{align*}

Calculate the following whenever defined. Otherwise state
\textbf{undefined} and include a brief explanation.

$\displaystyle A^{-1}$

sols:
Using the hint, we have that

$A^{-1} = \frac{1}{(1)(8)-(3)(3)}\begin{bmatrix}
8 & -3 \\ -3 & 1
\end{bmatrix}
= -1\begin{bmatrix}
8 & -3 \\ -3 & 1
\end{bmatrix}
= \begin{bmatrix}
-8 & 3 \\ 3 & -1
\end{bmatrix}$
